<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>21/05</p>
</div></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Payments from clo=
sed accounts should also be shown in the listing.</p><p>This needs <strong>=
payment EXP API</strong> to have a <strong>separate Mesh secret</strong> fo=
r this feature to hold both <strong>open and closed accounts</strong> in it=
.</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">To enable this featu=
re have payments for both open and <u>closed </u>accounts.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Payments from clo=
sed accounts will not be possible for the first release. <span class=3D"inl=
ine-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"1b2696e8-e3de-43db-89d1-f391d6415612">Uplif=
t is required later</span>.</p><p>This means we can re-use the existing lis=
t of accounts in the Mesh secret</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-username=3D"F079288" =
href=3D"/display/~F079288" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1415102363" data-link=
ed-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-=
url=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au">Melinda Jamieson</a>&nbsp;</p=
>
</div></td>
</tr>
